# Work dialogue.
# Format: see data/dialogue/school.dlg for the full spec.
# Trailing backslash joins onto the next line into one page (one click).

[intro_job]
[i]The next day starts under fluorescent lights.[/i]
[i]Your job is simple: sort parts, match shapes, and do it quick.[/i]
[i]It's gruelling work. It's not difficult, but sometimes you wonder if your uncle purposefully gave you the most mind-numbing job in the factory.[/i]

[intro_head_box]
[i]Your uncle's office is one of the last rooms you pass before reaching the exit.[/i]
[i]A box at your feet nearly trips you, and it felt like kicking a rock. Looking down at it, it's marked 'trash' for the cleaning bots to take care of when they see it.[/i]
[i]Why not take a peak? It's trash after all, and your foot still hurts.[/i]
[i]Your heart spikes with fear for a split second before you quickly realize what your'e looking at.[/i]
[i]It's full of one of the bot's head segments.. an eye, a nose, a cheek.. Your uncle must've given up assembling this one. You wonder why...[/i]
[i]You stuff it in your backpack before anyone notices.[/i]
[i]Thoughts: ...Why am I doing this?[/i]


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# COMPLETION - shown after the player fills all four slots, before the
# "what do you do?" steal-or-leave prompt.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

[completion]
[i]Your shift's almost over.[/i] \
[i]The line's emptied out.[/i] \
[i]The supervisor wandered off ten minutes ago.[/i]

[i]A spare scrap of metal sits at the edge of the bin.[/i]
[i]It wouldn't be missed.[/i]
[i]Nobody's looking right now.[/i]

# The gold "what do you do?" prompt and the two button labels (exact button text)
# for the finish-or-steal choice at the end of the shift.
[completion.prompt]
What do you do?

[completion.finish]
FINISH SHIFT

[completion.steal]
POCKET A SCRAP


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WORK DISRUPTION - the scripted robot phone call that plays the first time the
# player finishes the upper-arm assembly minigame after the intro. The robot
# notices the phone's GPS is on and talks the player into pocketing the arm.
# This shift ends on the arm being stolen, so the usual scrap steal choice is
# skipped (see Work.gd). Plays over a placeholder background until its own art
# exists.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

[robot_work_disruption]
You feel your phone buzzing in your pocket. No caller ID, it's an unknown number…
You: Hello?
Her: You know your phone's GPS is on?
You: What?
Thoughts: Shit! I can NOT leave that on.
Thoughts: It's bad enough that she knows where I am- but next time it might be the cops who find out where I am.
You quickly shut off your GPS before responding.
Her: Oh you turned it off…
You: Yeah, I can't just have it on. My job isn't exactly legal.
Her: It isn't?
Thoughts: …
Thoughts: She wouldn't report me would she?
Thoughts: No… She'd be destroyed if the police found her. I wonder if she knows that.
You: Yeah, robots are illegal now. It's a risk working for my uncle, but it pays.
Thoughts: I wish it paid more…
Her: You should steal that arm.
You: What?
You turn the phone over and see the flash is on…
You: Did you hack my phone's camera??
Her: Yes. Why?
You: The flash's on.
Her: Oh.
The flash suddenly turns off.
Thoughts: This is super creepy.
You: Please don't spy on me…
Her: I'm bored.
Her: Steal the arm
You have to whisper so no one hears you.
You: I can't just take it! There are people around.
Her: No one's watching I can tell.
It's just then that you notice a blue light coming from a camera above you.
Thoughts: This is super freaky.
You wave to the camera.
Her: Stop goofing around and steal the arm now. While no one's looking.
You: Hey don't boss me around.
You pack the upper arm in your bag.
Her: That's a good boy
You: Shut up.
